He was initially sentenced to the maximum possible punishment, longer than what prosecutors had requested: 99 years." />
                    <meta name="socialpost4" content="Jorge Ruiz’s lawyers examined 17 car crash cases in Alabama’s 19th Circuit over 15 years. Most defendants got sentences of less than 15 years, even in cases involving multiple fatalities or high blood alcohol levels. 

Ruiz initially got 99 years." />
