<div class="highlights">
    <h3 class="highlights__heading">Reporting Highlights</h3>
    <ul class="highlights__list">
                    <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">Serious Charge: </span> Drivers are rarely charged with murder in fatal car crashes unless they have aggravating factors — such as past DUIs or excessive speed.</li>
            <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">Uncommon Plea Deal: </span> Unlike most people facing these charges in Alabama’s 19th Circuit Court, this defendant was not offered a plea deal for a lesser charge.</li>
            <li class="highlights__highlight"><span class="highlights__subheading">Unusual Suspect: </span> Years after the crash, attorneys involved in the case would attempt to shed light on why it went so differently than similar cases — and what they believe was bias.</li>
            </ul>
    <p class="highlights__disclaimer">
        These highlights were written by the reporters and editors who worked on this story. <span id="survey-placeholder"></span>
    </p>
</div>

